  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Introduction'
      title: Introduction
      number: 1
      content: "  Paul, an apostle (special messenger, personally chosen representative)
        of Christ Jesus (the Messiah) by the will of God, and Timothy our brother, 
        To the church of God which is at Corinth, and to all the saints (God\u2019s
        people) throughout Achaia (southern Greece):  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Grace to you and peace [inner calm and spiritual well-being] from
        God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Blessed [gratefully praised and adored] be the God and Father of
        our Lord Jesus Christ, the Father of mercies and the God of all comfort, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'who comforts and encourages us in every trouble so that we will be
        able to comfort and encourage those who are in any kind of trouble, with
        the comfort with which we ourselves are comforted by God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For just as Christ\u2019s sufferings are ours in abundance [as they
        overflow to His followers], so also our comfort [our reassurance, our encouragement,
        our consolation] is abundant through Christ [it is truly more than enough
        to endure what we must]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But if we are troubled and distressed, it is for your comfort and
        salvation; or if we are comforted and encouraged, it is for your comfort,
        which works [in you] when you patiently endure the same sufferings which
        we experience. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And our hope for you [our confident expectation of good for you]
        is firmly grounded [assured and unshaken], since we know that just as you
        share as partners in our sufferings, so also you share as partners in our
        comfort.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For we do not want you to be uninformed, brothers and sisters, about
        our trouble in [the west coast province of] Asia [Minor], how we were utterly
        weighed down, beyond our strength, so that we despaired even of life [itself]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Indeed, we felt within ourselves that we had received the sentence
        of death [and were convinced that we would die, but this happened] so that
        we would not trust in ourselves, but in God who raises the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He rescued us from so great a threat of death, and will continue
        to rescue us. On Him we have set our hope. And He will again rescue us [from
        danger and draw us near], '
      comments: []
    - name: "11: Paul\u2019s Integrity"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Integrity"
      number: 11
      content: 'while you join in helping us by your prayers. Then thanks will be
        given by many persons on our behalf for the gracious gift [of deliverance]
        granted to us through the prayers of many [believers].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'This is our [reason for] proud confidence: our conscience testifies
        that we have conducted ourselves in the world [in general], and especially
        toward you, with pure motives and godly sincerity, not in human wisdom, but
        in the grace of God [that is, His gracious lovingkindness that leads people
        to Christ and spiritual maturity]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For we write you nothing other than what you read and understand
        [there is no double meaning in what we say]. And I hope you will [accurately]
        understand [divine things] until the end; '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'just as you have [already] partially understood us, [and one day
        will recognize] that you can be proud of us just as we are of you, in the
        day of our Lord Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'It was with this confidence that I planned at first to visit you,
        so that you might receive twice a token of grace; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'that is, [I wanted] to visit you on my way to Macedonia, and [then]
        to come back to you [on my return] from Macedonia, and have you send me on
        my way to Judea. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So then, was I indecisive or capricious when I was [originally] planning
        this? Or the things I plan, do I plan in a self-serving way like a worldly
        man, ready to say, \u201CYes, yes\u201D and \u201CNo, no\u201D [at the same
        time]? "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But [as surely as] God is faithful and means what He says, our message
        to you is not \u201CYes\u201D and \u201CNo\u201D [at the same time]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For the Son of God, Jesus Christ, who was preached among you by us,
        by me, Silvanus, and Timothy, was not \u201CYes\u201D and \u201CNo,\u201D
        but has proved to be \u201CYes\u201D in Him [true and faithful, the divine
        \u201CYes\u201D affirming God\u2019s promises]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For as many as are the promises of God, in Christ they are [all answered]
        \u201CYes.\u201D So through Him we say our \u201CAmen\u201D to the glory
        of God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now it is God who establishes and confirms us [in joint fellowship]
        with you in Christ, and who has anointed us [empowering us with the gifts
        of the Spirit]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'it is He who has also put His seal on us [that is, He has appropriated
        us and certified us as His] and has given us the [Holy] Spirit in our hearts
        as a pledge [like a security deposit to guarantee the fulfillment of His
        promise of eternal life].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "But I call on God as my soul\u2019s witness, that it was to spare
        you [pain and discouragement] that I did not come again to Corinth\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "not that we rule [like dictators] over your faith, but rather we
        work with you for [the increase of] your joy; for in your faith you stand
        firm [in your strong conviction that Jesus of Nazareth\u2014the Messiah\u2014is
        the Son of God, through whom we obtain eternal salvation]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Reaffirm Your Love'
      title: Reaffirm Your Love
      number: 1
      content: '  But I made up my mind not to grieve you with another painful visit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For if I cause you grief [by a well-deserved rebuke], who then provides
        me enjoyment but the very one whom I have made sad? '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And I wrote this same thing to you, so that when I came, I would
        not be filled with sorrow by those who ought to make me glad, for I trusted
        in you and felt confident that my joy would be shared by all of you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For I wrote to you out of great distress and with an anguished heart,
        and with many tears, not to cause you sorrow but to make you realize the
        [overflowing] love which I have especially for you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But if someone has caused [all this] sorrow, he has caused it not
        to me, but in some degree\u2014not to put it too severely\u2014[he has distressed
        and grieved] all of you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For such a one this punishment by the majority is sufficient, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'so instead [of further rebuke, now] you should rather [graciously]
        forgive and comfort and encourage him, to keep him from being overwhelmed
        by excessive sorrow. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Therefore I urge you to reinstate him in your affections and reaffirm
        your love for him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For this was my purpose in writing, to see if you would stand the
        test, whether you are obedient and committed to following my instruction
        in all things. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'If you forgive anyone anything, I too forgive [that one]; and what
        I have forgiven, if I have forgiven anything, has been for your sake in the
        presence of [and with the approval of] Christ, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'to keep Satan from taking advantage of us; for we are not ignorant
        of his schemes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now when I arrived at Troas to preach the good news of Christ, even
        though a door [of opportunity] opened for me in the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'my spirit could not rest because I did not find my brother Titus
        there; so saying goodbye to them, I left for Macedonia.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But thanks be to God, who always leads us in triumph in Christ, and
        through us spreads and makes evident everywhere the sweet fragrance of the
        knowledge of Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For we are the sweet fragrance of Christ [which ascends] to God,
        [discernible both] among those who are being saved and among those who are
        perishing; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'to the latter one an aroma from death to death [a fatal, offensive
        odor], but to the other an aroma from life to life [a vital fragrance, living
        and fresh]. And who is adequate and sufficiently qualified for these things? '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "For we are not like many, [acting like merchants] peddling God\u2019s
        word [shortchanging and adulterating God\u2019s message]; but from pure [uncompromised]
        motives, as [commissioned and sent] from God, we speak [His message] in Christ
        in the sight of God."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ministers of a New Covenant'
      title: Ministers of a New Covenant
      number: 1
      content: '  Are we starting to commend ourselves again? Or do we need, like
        some [false teachers], letters of recommendation to you or from you? [No!] '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You are our letter [of recommendation], written in our hearts, recognized
        and read by everyone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You show that you are a letter from Christ, delivered by us, written
        not with ink but with the Spirit of the living God, not on tablets of stone
        but on tablets of human hearts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Such is the confidence and steadfast reliance and absolute trust
        that we have through Christ toward God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Not that we are sufficiently qualified in ourselves to claim anything
        as coming from us, but our sufficiency and qualifications come from God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He has qualified us [making us sufficient] as ministers of a new
        covenant [of salvation through Christ], not of the letter [of a written code]
        but of the Spirit; for the letter [of the Law] kills [by revealing sin and
        demanding obedience], but the Spirit gives life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now if the ministry of death, engraved in letters on stones [the
        covenant of the Law which led to death because of sin], came with such glory
        and splendor that the Israelites were not able to look steadily at the face
        of Moses because of its glory, [a brilliance] that was fading, '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'how will the ministry of the Spirit [the new covenant which allows
        us to be Spirit-filled] fail to be even more glorious and splendid? '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For if the ministry that brings condemnation [the old covenant, the
        Law] has glory, how much more does glory overflow in the ministry that brings
        righteousness [the new covenant which declares believers free of guilt and
        sets them apart for God\u2019s special purpose]! "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Indeed, what had glory [the Law], in this case no longer has glory
        because of the glory that surpasses it [the gospel]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For if that [Law] which fades away came with glory, how much more
        must that [gospel] which remains and is permanent abide in glory and splendor!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Since we have such a [glorious] hope and confident expectation, we
        speak with great courage, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'and we are not like Moses, who used to put a veil over his face so
        that the Israelites would not gaze at the end of the glory which was fading
        away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But [in fact] their minds were hardened [for they had lost the ability
        to understand]; for until this very day at the reading of the old covenant
        the same veil remains unlifted, because it is removed [only] in Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But to this day whenever Moses is read, a veil [of blindness] lies
        over their heart; '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'but whenever a person turns [in repentance and faith] to the Lord,
        the veil is taken away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now the Lord is the Spirit, and where the Spirit of the Lord is,
        there is liberty [emancipation from bondage, true freedom]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: And we all, with unveiled face, continually seeing as in a mirror
        the glory of the Lord, are progressively being transformed into His image
        from [one degree of] glory to [even more] glory, which comes from the Lord,
        [who is] the Spirit.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Paul\u2019s Apostolic Ministry"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Apostolic Ministry"
      number: 1
      content: '  Therefore, since we have this ministry, just as we received mercy
        [from God, granting us salvation, opportunities, and blessings], we do not
        get discouraged nor lose our motivation. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "But we have renounced the disgraceful things hidden because of shame;
        not walking in trickery or adulterating the word of God, but by stating the
        truth [openly and plainly], we commend ourselves to everyone\u2019s conscience
        in the sight of God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But even if our gospel is [in some sense] hidden [behind a veil],
        it is hidden [only] to those who are perishing; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'among them the god of this world [Satan] has blinded the minds of
        the unbelieving to prevent them from seeing the illuminating light of the
        gospel of the glory of Christ, who is the image of God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For we do not preach ourselves, but Jesus Christ as Lord, and ourselves
        [merely] as your bond-servants for Jesus\u2019 sake. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For God, who said, \u201CLet light shine out of darkness,\u201D is
        the One who has shone in our hearts to give us the Light of the knowledge
        of the glory and majesty of God [clearly revealed] in the face of Christ.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But we have this precious treasure [the good news about salvation]
        in [unworthy] earthen vessels [of human frailty], so that the grandeur and
        surpassing greatness of the power will be [shown to be] from God [His sufficiency]
        and not from ourselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'We are pressured in every way [hedged in], but not crushed; perplexed
        [unsure of finding a way out], but not driven to despair; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'hunted down and persecuted, but not deserted [to stand alone]; struck
        down, but never destroyed; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'always carrying around in the body the dying of Jesus, so that the
        [resurrection] life of Jesus also may be shown in our body. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For we who live are constantly [experiencing the threat of] being
        handed over to death for Jesus\u2019 sake, so that the [resurrection] life
        of Jesus also may be evidenced in our mortal body [which is subject to death]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So physical death is [actively] at work in us, but [spiritual] life
        [is actively at work] in you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Yet we have the same spirit of faith as he had, who wrote in Scripture,
        \u201CI believed, therefore I spoke.\u201D We also believe, therefore we
        also speak, "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'knowing that He who raised the Lord Jesus will also raise us with
        Jesus and will present us [along] with you in His presence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For all [these] things are for your sake, so that as [God\u2019s
        remarkable, undeserved] grace reaches to more and more people it may increase
        thanksgiving, to the glory of [our great] God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore we do not become discouraged [spiritless, disappointed,
        or afraid]. Though our outer self is [progressively] wasting away, yet our
        inner self is being [progressively] renewed day by day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For our momentary, light distress [this passing trouble] is producing
        for us an eternal weight of glory [a fullness] beyond all measure [surpassing
        all comparisons, a transcendent splendor and an endless blessedness]! '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: So we look not at the things which are seen, but at the things which
        are unseen; for the things which are visible are temporal [just brief and
        fleeting], but the things which are invisible are everlasting and imperishable.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Temporal and Eternal'
      title: The Temporal and Eternal
      number: 1
      content: '  For we know that if the earthly tent [our physical body] which
        is our house is torn down [through death], we have a building from God, a
        house not made with hands, eternal in the heavens. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For indeed in this house we groan, longing to be clothed with our
        [immortal, eternal] celestial dwelling, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'so that by putting it on we will not be found naked. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For while we are in this tent, we groan, being burdened [often weighed
        down, oppressed], not that we want to be unclothed [separated by death from
        the body], but to be clothed, so that what is mortal [the body] will be swallowed
        up by life [after the resurrection]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now He who has made us and prepared us for this very purpose is God,
        who gave us the [Holy] Spirit as a pledge [a guarantee, a down payment on
        the fulfillment of His promise].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So then, being always filled with good courage and confident hope,
        and knowing that while we are at home in the body we are absent from the
        Lord\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "for we walk by faith, not by sight [living our lives in a manner
        consistent with our confident belief in God\u2019s promises]\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'we are [as I was saying] of good courage and confident hope, and
        prefer rather to be absent from the body and to be at home with the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore, whether we are at home [on earth] or away from home [and
        with Him], it is our [constant] ambition to be pleasing to Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For we [believers will be called to account and] must all appear
        before the judgment seat of Christ, so that each one may be repaid for what
        has been done in the body, whether good or bad [that is, each will be held
        responsible for his actions, purposes, goals, motives\u2014the use or misuse
        of his time, opportunities and abilities].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore, since we know the fear of the Lord [and understand the
        importance of obedience and worship], we persuade people [to be reconciled
        to Him]. But we are plainly known to God [He knows everything about us];
        and I hope that we are plainly known also in your consciences [your God-given
        discernment]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'We are not commending ourselves to you again, but are giving you
        an occasion to be [rightfully] proud of us, so that you will have an answer
        for those who take pride in [outward] appearances [the virtues they pretend
        to have] rather than what is [actually] in heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'If we are out of our mind [just unstable fanatics as some critics
        say], it is for God; if we are in our right mind, it is for your benefit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For the love of Christ controls and compels us, because we have concluded
        this, that One died for all, therefore all died; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'and He died for all, so that all those who live would no longer live
        for themselves, but for Him who died and was raised for their sake.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So from now on we regard no one from a human point of view [according
        to worldly standards and values]. Though we have known Christ from a human
        point of view, now we no longer know Him in this way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Therefore if anyone is in Christ [that is, grafted in, joined to
        Him by faith in Him as Savior], he is a new creature [reborn and renewed
        by the Holy Spirit]; the old things [the previous moral and spiritual condition]
        have passed away. Behold, new things have come [because spiritual awakening
        brings a new life]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But all these things are from God, who reconciled us to Himself through
        Christ [making us acceptable to Him] and gave us the ministry of reconciliation
        [so that by our example we might bring others to Him], '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "that is, that God was in Christ reconciling the world to Himself,
        not counting people\u2019s sins against them [but canceling them]. And He
        has committed to us the message of reconciliation [that is, restoration to
        favor with God].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "So we are ambassadors for Christ, as though God were making His appeal
        through us; we [as Christ\u2019s representatives] plead with you on behalf
        of Christ to be reconciled to God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: He made Christ who knew no sin to [judicially] be sin on our behalf,
        so that in Him we would become the righteousness of God [that is, we would
        be made acceptable to Him and placed in a right relationship with Him by
        His gracious lovingkindness].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Their Ministry Commended'
      title: Their Ministry Commended
      number: 1
      content: "  Working together with Him, we strongly urge you not to receive
        God\u2019s grace in vain [by turning away from sound doctrine and His merciful
        kindness]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "For He says,\u201CAt the acceptable time (the time of grace) I listened
        to you,And I helped you on the day of salvation.\u201DBehold, now is \u201Cthe
        acceptable time,\u201D behold, now is \u201Cthe day of salvation\u201D\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "we put no obstruction in anyone\u2019s path, so that the ministry
        will not be discredited, "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'but we commend ourselves in every way as servants of God: in great
        endurance, in sufferings, in hardships, in distresses, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'in beatings, in imprisonments, in riots, in labors, in sleepless
        nights, in hunger, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'in purity and sincerity, in knowledge and spiritual insight, in patience,
        in kindness, in the Holy Spirit, in genuine love, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'in [speaking] the word of truth, in the power of God; by the weapons
        of righteousness for the right hand [like holding the sword to attack] and
        for the left [like holding the shield to defend], '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'amid glory and dishonor; by evil report and good report; branded
        as deceivers and yet [vindicated as] truthful; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'as unknown [to the world], yet well-known [by God and His people];
        as dying, yet we live; as punished, yet not killed; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'as sorrowful, yet always rejoicing; as poor, yet bestowing riches
        on many; as having nothing, yet possessing all things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'We are speaking freely to you, Corinthians [we are keeping nothing
        back], and our heart is opened wide. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'There is no limit to our affection for you, but you are limited in
        your own affection [for us]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now in the same way as a fair exchange [for our love toward you]\u2014I
        am speaking as [I would] to children\u2014open wide [your hearts] to us also.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Do not be unequally bound together with unbelievers [do not make
        mismatched alliances with them, inconsistent with your faith]. For what partnership
        can righteousness have with lawlessness? Or what fellowship can light have
        with darkness? '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'What harmony can there be between Christ and Belial (Satan)? Or what
        does a believer have in common with an unbeliever? '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "What agreement is there between the temple of God and idols? For
        we are the temple of the living God; just as God said:\u201CI will dwell
        among them and walk among them;And I will be their God, and they shall be
        My people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "So come out from among unbelievers and be separate,\u201D says the
        Lord,\u201CAnd do not touch what is unclean;And I will graciously receive
        you and welcome you [with favor],  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And I will be a Father to you,And you will be My sons and daughters,\u201DSays
        the Lord Almighty."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul Reveals His Heart'
      title: Paul Reveals His Heart
      number: 1
      content: "  Therefore, since we have these [great and wonderful] promises,
        beloved, let us cleanse ourselves from everything that contaminates body
        and spirit, completing holiness [living a consecrated life\u2014a life set
        apart for God\u2019s purpose] in the fear of God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Make room for us in your hearts; we have wronged no one, we have
        corrupted no one, we have cheated no one. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I do not say this to condemn you, for I have said before that you
        are [nested] in our hearts [and you will remain there] to die together and
        to live together [with us]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Great is my confidence in you; great is my pride and boasting on
        your behalf. I am filled [to the brim] with comfort; I am overflowing with
        joy in spite of all our trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For even when we arrived in Macedonia our bodies had no rest, but
        we were oppressed at every turn\u2014conflicts and disputes without, fears
        and dread within. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But God, who comforts and encourages the depressed and the disquieted,
        comforted us by the arrival of Titus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And not only by his arrival, but also by [his account of] the encouragement
        which he received in regard to you. He told us about your longing [for us],
        your mourning [over sin], and how eagerly you took my part and supported
        me, so that I rejoiced even more. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For even though I did grieve you with my letter, I do not regret
        it [now]; though I did regret it \u2014for I see that the letter hurt you,
        though only for a little while\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'yet I am glad now, not because you were hurt and made sorry, but
        because your sorrow led to repentance [and you turned back to God]; for you
        felt a grief such as God meant you to feel, so that you might not suffer
        loss in anything on our account. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For [godly] sorrow that is in accord with the will of God produces
        a repentance without regret, leading to salvation; but worldly sorrow [the
        hopeless sorrow of those who do not believe] produces death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For [you can look back and] see what an earnestness and authentic
        concern this godly sorrow has produced in you: what vindication of yourselves
        [against charges that you tolerate sin], what indignation [at sin], what
        fear [of offending God], what longing [for righteousness and justice], what
        passion [to do what is right], what readiness to punish [those who sin and
        those who tolerate sin]! At every point you have proved yourselves to be
        innocent in the matter. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So even though I wrote to you [as I did], it was not for the sake
        of the offender nor for the sake of the one offended, but in order to make
        evident to you before God how earnestly you do care for us [and your willingness
        to accept our authority]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'It is for this reason that we are comforted and encouraged.  And
        in addition to our comfort, we were especially delighted at the joy of Titus,
        because you have refreshed his spirit. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For if I have boasted to him at all concerning you, I was not disappointed.
        But just as everything we ever said to you was true, so our boasting [about
        you] to Titus has proved true also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'His affection is greater than ever as he remembers the obedience
        [to his guidance] that all of you exhibited, and how you received him with
        the greatest respect. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: I rejoice that in everything I have [perfect] confidence in you.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Great Generosity'
      title: Great Generosity
      number: 1
      content: '  Now, brothers and sisters, we want to tell you about the grace
        of God which has been evident in the churches of Macedonia [awakening in
        them a longing to contribute]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'for during an ordeal of severe distress, their abundant joy and their
        deep poverty [together] overflowed in the wealth of their lavish generosity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For I testify that according to their ability, and beyond their ability,
        they gave voluntarily, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'begging us insistently for the privilege of participating in the
        service for [the support of] the saints [in Jerusalem]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Not only [did they give materially] as we had hoped, but first they
        gave themselves to the Lord and to us [as His representatives] by the will
        of God [disregarding their personal interests and giving as much as they
        possibly could]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So we urged Titus that, as he began it, he should also complete this
        gracious work among you as well.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But just as you excel in everything, [and lead the way] in faith,
        in speech, in knowledge, in genuine concern, and in your love for us, see
        that you excel in this gracious work [of giving] also. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I am not saying this as a command [to dictate to you], but to prove,
        by [pointing out] the enthusiasm of others, the sincerity of your love as
        well. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For you are recognizing [more clearly] the grace of our Lord Jesus
        Christ [His astonishing kindness, His generosity, His gracious favor], that
        though He was rich, yet for your sake He became poor, so that by His poverty
        you might become rich (abundantly blessed). '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I give you my opinion in this matter: this is to your advantage,
        who were the first to begin a year ago not only to take action [to help the
        believers in Jerusalem], but also [the first] to desire to do it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So now finish this, so that your eagerness in desiring it may be
        equaled by your completion of it, according to your ability. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For if the eagerness [to give] is there, it is acceptable according
        to what one has, not according to what he does not have. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For it is not [intended] that others be relieved [of their responsibility]
        and that you be burdened [unfairly], but that there be equality [in sharing
        the burden]\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'at this present time your surplus [over necessities] is going to
        supply their need, so that [at some other time] their surplus may be given
        to supply your need, that there may be equality; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "as it is written [in Scripture], \u201CHe who  gathered  much did
        not have too much, and he who  gathered  little did not lack.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But thanks be to God who puts the same genuine concern for you in
        the heart of Titus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For Titus not only accepted our appeal, but was so very interested
        in you that he has gone to visit you of his own accord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And we have sent along with him the brother who is praised in the
        gospel [ministry] throughout all the churches; '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and not only this, but he has also been appointed by the churches
        to travel with us in regard to this gracious offering which we are administering
        for the glory of the Lord Himself, and to show our eagerness [as believers
        to help one another]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'We are taking precaution so that no one will [find anything with
        which to] discredit us in our administration of this generous gift. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For we have regard for what is honorable [and above suspicion], not
        only in the sight of the Lord, but also in the sight of men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'We have sent with them our brother, whom we have often tested and
        found to be diligent in many things, but who is now even more diligent [than
        ever] because of his great confidence in you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'As for Titus, he is my partner and fellow worker in your service;
        and as for the [other two] brothers, they are [special] messengers of the
        churches, a glory and credit to Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Therefore, show these men, in the sight of the churches, the proof
        of your love and our reason for being proud of you.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Gives Most'
      title: God Gives Most
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it is unnecessary for me to write to you about the offering
        [that is to be made] for the saints [in Jerusalem]; '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'for I know your eagerness [to promote this cause], and I have [proudly]
        boasted to the people of Macedonia about it, telling them that Achaia has
        been prepared since last year [for this contribution], and your enthusiasm
        has inspired the majority of them [to respond]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Still, I am sending the brothers [on to you], so that our pride in
        you may not be an empty boast in this case, and so that you may be prepared,
        just as I told them you would be; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "otherwise, if any Macedonians come with me and find you unprepared,
        we\u2014to say nothing of yourselves\u2014will be humiliated for being so
        confident. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'That is why I thought it necessary to urge these brothers to go to
        you [before I come] and make arrangements in advance for this generous, previously
        promised gift of yours, so that it would be ready, not as something extorted
        [or wrung out of you], but as a [voluntary and] generous gift.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now [remember] this: he who sows sparingly will also reap sparingly,
        and he who sows generously [that blessings may come to others] will also
        reap generously [and be blessed]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Let each one give [thoughtfully and with purpose] just as he has
        decided in his heart, not grudgingly or under compulsion, for God loves a
        cheerful giver [and delights in the one whose heart is in his gift]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And God is able to make all grace [every favor and earthly blessing]
        come in abundance to you, so that you may always [under all circumstances,
        regardless of the need] have complete sufficiency in everything [being completely
        self-sufficient in Him], and have an abundance for every good work and act
        of charity. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "As it is written and forever remains written,\u201CHe [the benevolent
        and generous person] scattered abroad, he gave to the poor,His righteousness
        endures forever!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now He who provides seed for the sower and bread for food will provide
        and multiply your seed for sowing [that is, your resources] and increase
        the harvest of your righteousness [which shows itself in active goodness,
        kindness, and love]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You will be enriched in every way so that you may be generous, and
        this [generosity, administered] through us is producing thanksgiving to God
        [from those who benefit]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For the ministry of this service (offering) is not only supplying
        the needs of the saints (God\u2019s people), but is also overflowing through
        many expressions of thanksgiving to God. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Because of this act of ministry, they will glorify God for your obedience
        to the gospel of Christ which you confess, as well as for your generous participation
        [in this gift] for them and for all [the other believers in need], '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "and they also long for you while they pray on your behalf, because
        of the surpassing measure of God\u2019s grace [His undeserved favor, mercy,
        and blessing which is revealed] in you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: Now thanks be to God for His indescribable gift [which is precious
        beyond words]!
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul Describes Himself'
      title: Paul Describes Himself
      number: 1
      content: "  Now I, Paul, urge you by the gentleness and graciousness of Christ\u2014I
        who am meek [so they say] when with you face to face, but bold [outspoken
        and fearless] toward you when absent! "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I ask that when I do come I will not be driven to the boldness that
        I intend to show toward those few who regard us as if we walked according
        to the flesh [like men without the Spirit]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For though we walk in the flesh [as mortal men], we are not carrying
        on our [spiritual] warfare according to the flesh and using the weapons of
        man. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The weapons of our warfare are not physical [weapons of flesh and
        blood]. Our weapons are divinely powerful for the destruction of fortresses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'We are destroying sophisticated arguments and every exalted and proud
        thing that sets itself up against the [true] knowledge of God, and we are
        taking every thought and purpose captive to the obedience of Christ, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'being ready to punish every act of disobedience, when your own obedience
        [as a church] is complete.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "You are looking [only] at the outward appearance of things. If anyone
        is confident that he is Christ\u2019s, he should reflect and consider this,
        that just as he is Christ\u2019s, so too are we. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For even though I boast rather freely about the authority the Lord
        gave us for building you up and not for destroying you, I will not be ashamed
        [of the truth], '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'nor do I want to seem to be trying to frighten you with my letters; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "for they say, \u201CHis letters are weighty and forceful and impressive,
        but his personal presence is unimpressive and his speech contemptible [of
        no account].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Let such people realize that what we say by word in letters when
        we are absent, is the same as what we are in action when present.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'We do not have the audacity to put ourselves in the same class or
        compare ourselves with some who [supply testimonials to] commend themselves.
        When they measure themselves by themselves and compare themselves with themselves,
        they lack wisdom and behave like fools. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'We, on the other hand, will not boast beyond our proper limit, but
        [will keep] within the limits of our commission (territory, authority) which
        God has granted to us as a measure, which reaches and includes even you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'We are not overstepping the limits of our province, as if we did
        not [legitimately] reach to you, for we were the [very] first to come even
        as far as you with the good news of Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'We do not go beyond our proper limit, boasting in the work of other
        men, but we have the hope that as your faith [in Christ and His divine power]
        continues to grow, our field among you may be greatly expanded [but still
        within the limits of our commission], '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "so that we may preach the gospel even in the lands beyond you, but
        not to boast in work already accomplished in another one\u2019s field of
        activity. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "However, \u201CLet him who boasts boast in the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: For it is not he who commends and praises himself who is approved
        [by God], but it is the one whom the Lord commends and praises.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Paul Defends His Apostleship'
      title: Paul Defends His Apostleship
      number: 1
      content: '  I wish you would bear with me [while I indulge] in a little foolishness;
        but indeed you are bearing with me [as you read this]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I am jealous for you with a godly jealousy because I have promised
        you to one husband, to present you as a pure virgin to Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'But I am afraid that, even as the serpent beguiled Eve by his cunning,
        your minds may be corrupted and led away from the simplicity of [your sincere
        and] pure devotion to Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For [you seem willing to allow it] if one comes and preaches another
        Jesus whom we have not preached, or if you receive a different spirit from
        the one you received, or a different gospel from the one you accepted. You
        tolerate all this beautifully [welcoming the deception]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Yet I consider myself in no way inferior to the [so-called] super-apostles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But even if I am unskilled in speaking, yet I am not [untrained]
        in knowledge [I know what I am talking about]; but we have made this evident
        to you in every way, in all things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Or did I [perhaps] sin by humbling myself so that you might be exalted
        and honored, because I preached God\u2019s gospel to you free of charge? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I robbed other churches by accepting [more than their share of] financial
        support for my ministry to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And when I was with you and ran short [financially], I did not burden
        any of you; for what I needed was fully supplied by the brothers (Silas and
        Timothy) who came from Macedonia (the church at Philippi). So I kept myself
        from being a burden to you in any way, and will continue to do so. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'As the truth of Christ is in me, my boast [of independence] will
        not be silenced in the regions of Achaia (southern Greece). '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Why? Because I do not love you [or wish you well, or have regard
        for your welfare]? God knows [that I do]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But what I am doing I will keep doing, [for I am determined to keep
        this independence] in order to cut off the claim of those who want an opportunity
        to be regarded just as we are in the things they brag about. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For such men are counterfeit apostles, deceitful workers, masquerading
        as apostles of Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And no wonder, since Satan himself masquerades as an angel of light. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So it is no great surprise if his servants also masquerade as servants
        of righteousness, but their end will correspond with their deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'I repeat then, let no one think that I am foolish; but even if you
        do, at least accept me as foolish, so that I too may boast a little. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'What I say in this confident boasting, I say not as the Lord would
        [with His authority], but foolishly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Since many boast [of worldly things and brag] about human accomplishments,
        I will boast too. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'For you, being so wise, gladly tolerate and accept the foolish [like
        me]! '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For you tolerate it if anyone makes you his slave; or devours you
        and your possessions; or takes advantage of you; or acts presumptuously;
        or hits you in the face. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "To my shame, I must say, we have been too weak [in comparison to
        those pseudo-apostles who take advantage of you].  But in whatever anyone
        else dares to boast\u2014I am speaking foolishly\u2014I also dare to boast. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Are they Hebrews? So am I. Are they Israelites? So am I. Are they
        descendants of Abraham? So am I. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Are they [self-proclaimed] servants of Christ?\u2014I am speaking
        as if I were out of my mind\u2014I am more so [for I exceed them]; with far
        more labors, with far more imprisonments, beaten times without number, and
        often in danger of death. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Five times I received from the Jews thirty-nine lashes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Three times I was beaten with rods, once I was stoned. Three times
        I was shipwrecked, a night and a day I have spent adrift on the sea; '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'many times on journeys, [exposed to] danger from rivers, danger from
        bandits, danger from my own countrymen, danger from the Gentiles, danger
        in the city, danger in the wilderness, danger on the sea, danger among those
        posing as believers; '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'in labor and hardship, often unable to sleep, in hunger and thirst,
        often [driven to] fasting [for lack of food], in cold and exposure [without
        adequate clothing]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Besides those external things, there is the daily [inescapable] pressure
        of my concern for all the churches. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Who is weak, and I do not feel [his] weakness? Who is made to sin,
        and I am not on fire [with sorrow and concern]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'If I must boast, I will boast of the things that reveal my weakness
        [the things by which I am made weak in the eyes of my opponents]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The God and Father of the Lord Jesus, He who is blessed and to be
        praised forevermore, knows that I am not lying. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'In Damascus the governor (ethnarch) under King Aretas guarded the
        city of Damascus in order to arrest me, '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: and I was [actually] let down in a basket through a window in the
        wall, and slipped through his fingers.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Paul\u2019s Vision"
      title: "Paul\u2019s Vision"
      number: 1
      content: '  It is necessary to boast, though nothing is gained by it; but I
        will go on to visions and revelations of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "I know a man in Christ who fourteen years ago\u2014whether in the
        body I do not know, or out of the body I do not know, [only] God knows\u2014such
        a man was caught up to the third heaven. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And I know that such a man\u2014whether in the body or out of the
        body I do not know, [only] God knows\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'was caught up into Paradise and heard inexpressible words which man
        is not permitted to speak [words too sacred to tell]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'On behalf of such a man [and his experiences] I will boast; but in
        my own behalf I will not boast, except in regard to my weaknesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: A Thorn in the Flesh'
      title: A Thorn in the Flesh
      number: 6
      content: 'If I wish to boast, I will not be foolish, because I will be speaking
        the truth. But I abstain [from it], so that no one will credit me with more
        than [is justified by what] he sees in me or hears from me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Because of the surpassing greatness and extraordinary nature of the
        revelations [which I received from God], for this reason, to keep me from
        thinking of myself as important, a thorn in the flesh was given to me, a
        messenger of Satan, to torment and harass me\u2014to keep me from exalting
        myself! "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Concerning this I pleaded with the Lord three times that it might
        leave me; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "but He has said to me, <JESUS>\u201CMy grace is sufficient for you</JESUS>
        [My lovingkindness and My mercy are more than enough\u2014always available\u2014regardless
        of the situation]; <JESUS>for</JESUS> [My] <JESUS>power is being perfected</JESUS>
        [and is completed and shows itself most effectively] <JESUS>in</JESUS> [your]
        <JESUS>weakness.\u201D</JESUS> Therefore, I will all the more gladly boast
        in my weaknesses, so that the power of Christ [may completely enfold me and]
        may dwell in me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So I am well pleased with weaknesses, with insults, with distresses,
        with persecutions, and with difficulties, for the sake of Christ; for when
        I am weak [in human strength], then I am strong [truly able, truly powerful,
        truly drawing from God\u2019s strength].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now I have become foolish; you have forced me [by questioning my
        apostleship]. Actually I should have been commended by you [instead of being
        treated disdainfully], for I was not inferior to those super-apostles, even
        if I am nobody. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The signs that indicate a genuine apostle were performed among you
        fully and most patiently\u2014signs and wonders and miracles. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For in what respect were you treated as inferior to the rest of the
        churches, except [for the fact] that I did not burden you [with my financial
        support]? Forgive me [for doing you] this injustice!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Now for the third time I am ready to visit you. I will not burden
        you [financially], because I do not want what is yours [not your money or
        your possessions], but you. For children are not responsible to save up for
        their parents, but parents for their children. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But I will very gladly spend [my own resources] and be utterly spent
        for your souls. If I love you greatly, am I to be loved less [by you]? '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But be that as it may, I did not burden you [with my support]. But
        [some say that] I was sly and took you by trickery. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Did I take advantage of you or make any money off you through any
        of the messengers I sent you? [Certainly not!] '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I urged Titus to go, and I sent the brother with him. Titus did not
        take advantage of you, did he? [No!] Did we not conduct ourselves in the
        same spirit and walk in the same steps? [Of course!]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'All this time you have been thinking that we are [merely] defending
        ourselves to you. It is in the sight of God that we have been speaking [as
        one] in Christ; and everything, dearly beloved, is to strengthen you [spiritually]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For I am afraid that perhaps when I come I may find you not to be
        as I wish, and that you may find me not as you wish\u2014that perhaps there
        may be strife, jealousy, angry tempers, disputes, slander, gossip, arrogance
        and disorder; "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: I am afraid that when I come again my God may humiliate me before
        you, and I may mourn over many of those who have sinned in the past and not
        repented of the impurity, sexual immorality and decadence which they formerly
        practiced.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Examine Yourselves'
      title: Examine Yourselves
      number: 1
      content: '  This is the third time that I am visiting you. Every fact shall
        be sustained  and  confirmed by the testimony of two or three witnesses. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I have already warned those who have sinned in the past and all the
        rest as well, and I warn them now even though I am absent [from you] as I
        did when I was with you the second time, that if I come back I will not spare
        anyone,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'since you seek [forensic] proof that Christ is speaking in and through
        me. He is not weak or ineffective in dealing with you, but powerful within
        you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For even though He was crucified in weakness [yielding Himself],
        yet He lives [resurrected] by the power of God [His Father]. For we too are
        weak in Him [as He was humanly weak], yet we are alive and well [in fellowship]
        with Him because of the power of God directed toward you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Test and evaluate yourselves to see whether you are in the faith
        and living your lives as [committed] believers. Examine yourselves [not me]!
        Or do you not recognize this about yourselves [by an ongoing experience]
        that Jesus Christ is in you\u2014unless indeed you fail the test and are
        rejected as counterfeit? "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But I hope you will acknowledge that we do not fail the test nor
        are we to be rejected. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But I pray to God that you may do nothing wrong. Not so that we [and
        our teaching] may appear to be approved, but that you may continue doing
        what is right, even though we [by comparison] may seem to have failed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For we can do nothing against the truth, but only for the truth [and
        the gospel\u2014the good news of salvation]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "We are glad when we are weak [since God\u2019s power comes freely
        through us], but you [by comparison] are strong. We also pray for this, that
        you be made complete [fully restored, growing and maturing in godly character
        and spirit\u2014pleasing your heavenly Father by the life you live]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For this reason I am writing these things while absent from you,
        so that when I come, I will not need to deal severely [with you], in my use
        of the authority which the Lord has given me [to be used] for building you
        up and not for tearing you down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Finally, believers, rejoice! Be made complete [be what you should
        be], be comforted, be like-minded, live in peace [enjoy the spiritual well-being
        experienced by believers who walk closely with God]; and the God of love
        and peace [the source of lovingkindness] will be with you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Greet one another with a holy kiss. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "All God\u2019s people greet you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: The grace of the Lord Jesus Christ and the love of God, and the fellowship
        of the Holy Spirit be with you all.
      comments: []
